Comment on
    Kidney Int. 2018 Sep;94(3):567-581.

A good understanding of disease burden is the first step in formulating a 
response to it. Analysis of the Global Burden of Disease 2016 dataset shows an 
87% rise in the global burden of chronic kidney disease and a doubling of 
chronic kidney disease deaths between 1990 and 2016. Countries with a lower 
level of socioeconomic development and poorer access to quality health care 
experience a higher chronic kidney disease burden. Reductions in global 
disability-adjusted life-years over time indicate progress, but deviations from 
this trend in some geographies present a call to action.

